<plot>As with many things, it's the people, their stories and their experiences that can best describe life aboard a narrowboat. Join us in this programme as we meet a wealth of characters and personalities who are united in their love of days spent on the canal. Life on a narrowboat may be taken at a slower pace but it is never dull - missing bridges, ghostly goings-on, undiscovered murders, and more than a fair share of people falling overboard: these are the tales of life on the waterways.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?389912</url></doc>
